metadata.name: Ebi-Eré
metadata.description:
I am whole, I am beautiful because I have you.
You brought me beauty,
My scars are now a symbol of my triumph.

I am blessed to be the vessel that bears you.
You have made me a goddess.
For of my flesh and blood, you are formed.

My gift, my greatest pride, my sweet angel.
I can feel all you bring,
You bring heaven to me,
An omen of tranquillity.

I am whole now,
I have you.
